g^n &amp;:= \underbrace{g \cdot g \cdots g}_{n\text{ times}}.\\
g^{-n} &amp;:= \underbrace{g^{-1} \cdot g^{-1} \cdots g^{-1}}_{n\text{ times}}\\
g^0 &amp;:= e.
\end{split}\]
@claim
@newcol
Let $G$ be a group.
<ol>
