<p><blockquote><h5>Theorem.</h5>[First Isomorphism Theorem]
Let $\phi : G \ra G'$ be a homomorphism of groups.
Then, $\ker \phi$ is a normal subgroup of $G$, and $G/\ker \phi$ is isomorphic to $\im \phi$.
<p></blockquote><hr>
<b>Shown in class.</b>


